"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-asher-smith-neita-team-gb-relay-b1175152.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Dina Asher-Smithbelieves she and her fellowTeam GBsprinters can make their mark and come away with a medal in the 4x100m relays at the2024 Olympics.  After what has been a difficultOlympic Games, Asher-Smith returned to some of her best form in the final of the 200monly to be denied a bronze medal by just two hundredths of a secondon Tuesday night.  Asher-Smith had been told by her coach Edrick 'Flo' Floreal before the race, \\\"if you die you die, just get out and keep going\\\".  That do-or-die attitude very nearly got her a medal after a 100m performance that was well off her best and left her and her coaching team scratching their heads. Now, she plans to leave Paris with a piece of silverware.  \\\"I am really excited for the relay,\\\" she said. \\\"I think it's going to be a fun couple of days for us.  \\\"Women's sprinting is really incredible right now. It's a great time to be a female sprinter.\\\"  The Americans look set to be the strongest quartet in the relays while the Jamaicans have been shorn of some of their best pace women through injury.  Olympics 2024 medal table and latest count today  Olympics 2024: Every Team GB medal winner at the Paris Games so far  Asher-Smith said she would reflect on her two individual races as a stepping stone following a first season training outside the UK in Texas with a new coach after splitting with lifetime coach John Blackie.  \\\"For a first year with a new coach, I think this is a great platform to build from,\\\" she said. \\\"Overall, I am happy because I have known I have been in a great place for this whole season.\\\"  Daryll Neitawas just a further hundredth of a second behind in the 200m in fifth following on from an impressive fourth in the 100m.  Neita revealed she had had a last-minute pep talk from Keely Hodgkinson, complete with a gold medal around her neck, telling her, \\\"just leave nothing to chance, just give it your all\\\".  She added: \\\"It's amazing when you have got team-mates who are so open to share because not everybody might be so open. Keely is so open and inspiring, it's a really good energy to be around.  \\\"I was so close and you just want one of those medals. But I am so proud of myself and I know my time is coming. I have to be a little bit more patient. I am hungry, I fought it all the way to the line. Ultimately, I do not have the medal around my neck.\\\"  Asher-Smith and Neita, who have been rivals since they were young girls, will reunite to become the fulcrum of the British sprint relay team in Paris. The heats are on Thursday morning with the final on Friday evening.  Tuesday night's 200m final was won by American Gabby Thomas in a time of 21.83sec.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"